A form four student was on Wednesday night shot dead by thugs in Subukia, Nakuru county.The student from Maryland Secondary School was shot outside an M-Pesa shop as three armed thugs fled from police. The shop is less than 600 metres from Subukia police station and the deputy county commissioner&rsquo;s office. Subukia police boss Alex Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a yesterday said he led a team of officers in hunting the thugs in estates and farms immediately after the 8pm shooting. &ldquo;The three thugs invaded a chemist, where they ordered the owner to hand over all the day&rsquo;s sales and his mobile phone as customers waited,&rdquo; he said.Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a said the proprietor complied after one of the suspects pointed an AK-47 rifle at him.The suspects then moved to a nearby M-Pesa shop, but dropped a bag with the money and the mobile phone they had stolen from the chemist owner. &ldquo;As they entered the M-Pesa shop, which also houses an Equity agent outlet, they shot the male student from behind as he attempted to flee when he saw them,&rdquo; Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a said. The thugs fled on foot. The student, identified only as Mwangi, died at Subukia Subcounty Hospital. The incident sparked tension in the area and business premises were hurriedly shut. Police ordered boda boda operators to go home as they launched a manhunt for the robbers.